\section*{PREVENTION}
-Tetanus toxoid to all pregnant women
Education on hygiene
-Appropriate cord care

\section*{MANX}
-
Sedate baby by
Phenobarbitone $15 \mathrm{mg} / \mathrm{kg}$ start
Diazepam $0.2 \mathrm{mg} / \mathrm{kg}$ over 3 minutes. Repeat every $30 \mathrm{~min} x$ 3 doses
Do not exceed $2 \mathrm{mg} / \mathrm{kg} / 24 \mathrm{hrs}$
Clean cord thoroughly
Pass a NGT for feeding

\section*{SUBSEQUENT CARE}
- Nurse the baby in a quiet dark room
-Avoid too much handling
- Keep umbilical cord clean \& dry
-Paint cord with povidine iodine or spirit
-Feed EBM through NGT
-Phenobarbitone $5 \mathrm{mg} / \mathrm{kg} /$ day in 2 doses
-Antibiotics iv crystalline penicillin 100 000u/kg/day in 2 doses
- Monitor v/s - watch resp.
Counsel the mother.
Refer to ICU
Immunize baby after recovery.
